{"type":"message","id":"52b51639","parentId":"95fc5afd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:26:56.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API endpoint /get_time returns 404, which means the key is truncated in the config. The header shows `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` which is truncated. But the actual key in /tmp/sorftime_key.txt is correct.\n\nThe issue is the mcporter config has a truncated key in the header. I need to fix the config file to use the complete key, then the MCP server will work.\n\nBut wait - mcporter is just the MCP client configuration. The actual MCP server is managed by OpenClaw. Let me check how the sorftime MCP is configured in OpenClaw and how it's being called.\n\n\nActually, looking at the MEMORY.md entry about the bug fix - the key was being truncated when stored in a shell variable. The workaround was to read from /tmp/sorftime_key.txt. But the mcporter.json config is what's being used, and it has the truncated key. I need to update mcporter.json with the complete key.\n","thinkingSignature":"f68378b3067d6d9809ab04f0b40824f12a9fdb156009e1da027df8c4554ff718"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n问题是配置文件里的 key 被截断了（`rhblyi…qt09`），导致认证失败。我来修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_48efzio51lnp_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"sorftime-mcp\": {\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://mcp.sorftime.com/\",\n      \"headers\": {\n        \"Authorization\": \"Bearer…qt09\",\n        \"accept\": \"application/json, text/event-stream\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}","path":"/home/halei/workspace-tts/config/mcporter.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":505,"output":350,"cacheRead":49536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50391,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453608027,"responseId":"066ec3e86235f0ac0518a4ab463cdc8f"}}
