{"type":"message","id":"edf4cca9","parentId":"87dfaac2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:27:43.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the key is `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` which is the full key. Now the mcporter config has the full key.\n\nBut wait - I see the config now shows `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` with the ellipsis character (…), not the full key text. Let me look more carefully.\n\nActually `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` is exactly what we want - the full key is `rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09`, so `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` IS complete because the ellipsis is the literal character in the key... no wait.\n \nLet me trace through this more carefully. The full key `rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09` is 28 characters after \"Bearer \", but `rhblyi…qt09` is only 11 characters total. So the config file is definitely truncated - the ellipsis is a visual indicator that something was cut off, not the actual character in the key. The partial key `rhblyi…qt09` is only 11 characters long when the full key should be much longer. I need to figure out the actual mechanism being used here and test what happens when I send the truncated version versus the complete key to the MCP server.\n","thinkingSignature":"5c1a4988a70f35ec910fe4165f50de4ad9b630c51c8498683635e6a22e40c05a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9dfmz48sn970_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test with the full key directly\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" \\\n     -H \"accept: application/json\" \\\n     \"https://mcp.sorftime.com/get_time\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":200,"output":366,"cacheRead":51136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51702,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453656625,"responseId":"066ec418fee8345395fb81b57e791963"}}
