{"type":"message","id":"9c117bf9","parentId":"509206e5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:29:03.866Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tools are there but the key in the config is being read as truncated \"Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" (the \"…\" character hides the full key). But when I checked the actual API it returned \"NotAuthorization\" even with what appears to be the correct key format.\n\nThe problem is the config has \"Bearer…qt09\" which is NOT the full key. The actual key is \"rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09\". The config shows \"Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" - wait, but I confirmed earlier that '90sux' is in the value, so the value might actually be correct but just displaying with \"...\" in the middle for some reason.\n \nLooking at the actual character count and comparing what I'm seeing to the real key, I'm realizing the mcporter config might be getting the full key through some other path or reading mechanism that's different from how it's being displayed. Let me trace where mcporter is actually getting the key from - it's reading from `/home/halei/workspace-tts/config/mcporter.json` via the --config flag, but the workspace-tts config shows truncated values.\n\nI need to figure out whether mcporter has its own separate config at `~/.mcporter/mcporter.json` or if it's reading from the same file, and whether there's a way to properly update the Authorization header so mcporter can actually call the tools successfully.\n","thinkingSignature":"736da9d78d34bd5d2ac13cef409fa0b73bc14ac57850451abbe18270e4fbb7cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vk7ca068jkzy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter config get sorftime-mcp 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6399,"output":333,"cacheRead":53184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59916,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453735193,"responseId":"066ec