{"type":"message","id":"e7d1832a","parentId":"21e8480f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:29:12.152Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config shows `Bearer rhblyi…qt09` but the actual value in the file is `Bearer rhblyi…qt09`. The display is truncating it. So the actual key IS correct in the file.\n\nThe MCP server itself has a bug where it returns \"授权失败\" for most calls but works for `get_time`. This is a sorftime MCP server issue.\n\nLet me check if there's something different about how the MCP is configured vs how mcporter is calling it. The fact that `get_time` works but other tools don't suggests the authorization is actually working (get_time returns correct time), but something else is going on.\n\n\nLooking back at the MEMO, the `get_time` function was always working fine—it was the other APIs that were returning \"Authentication required\". So the current behavior matches what we saw then: get_time works while everything else fails. The key in the config file is complete and correct, but the sorftime MCP server is still returning authorization errors for most tools. This is an MCP-level issue, not a configuration problem.\n","thinkingSignature":"4f6a27697849f102a33889c02fbc56e352bb4c995361e8d6891de9099a93290e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bppezi15a9lc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://mcp.sorftime.com/\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" \\\n  -H \"accept: application/json, text/event-stream\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"get_time\",\"arguments\":{}},\"id\":2}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":173,"output":361,"cacheRead":59520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60054,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453744531,"responseId":"066ec47012cafc73