{"type":"message","id":"5aab1b8b","parentId":"a7eb7e1e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:29:57.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the API works but there's no data for that search term. This confirms the MCP is working fine.\n\nNow I see the user has been complaining that the selection agent has been failing for many days with no data. The problem is likely:\n\n1. The config file key truncation issue - which we've found and seems to have been present since at least May 24\n2. Even after that was supposedly fixed by reading from /tmp/sorftime_key.txt, the actual mcporter config still had the truncated key\n\nNow let me verify the current state - mcporter IS working (tested get_time and potential_product successfully). But the user says many days of no successful selections.\n\nLet me think about what the selection workflow actually looks like. Based on MEMORY.md:\n- They use sorftime MCP to get product data\n- Then write to a Feishu bitable\n\nLet me check if there's a script or automated workflow that was supposed to run. The user says \"好多天选品不成功\" (many days selection not successful).\n\nLet me check the cron jobs and any recent activity.\n","thinkingSignature":"c58a2c7efb7c142bddb03d6147049af7ce770dbf77f9a4015bb4fb63fdda011a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t65j6be53sxf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"crontab -l 2>/dev/null; cat ~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t65j6be53sxf_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/workspace-tts/docs/SOP.md 2>/dev/null | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":157,"output":328,"cacheRead":59904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60389,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453780212,"responseId":"066ec4942ade6ecfbfc238fc842e753d"}}
