{"type":"message","id":"f318fba9","parentId":"a7162475","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:30:14.973Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the MCP is working. Now let me try the full workflow - search for potential products. Let me use shopee_product_search since that seems most relevant to the TK/东南亚 strategy, and it's more likely to show trending products.\n\nWait, but I need to think about what the user actually wants. They said \"选品不成功，没有数据\" - they're frustrated that product selection keeps failing and there's no data.\n\nLet me think about this from scratch. The user's complaint is:\n1. 天天失败 - daily failures\n2. 好多天选品不成功 - many days of failed product selection\n3. 没有数据 - no data\n\n\n4. The core issue might be that I'm making assumptions about which tools to use without actually checking what OpenClaw has configured. The mcporter setup is separate from OpenClaw's MCP server configuration, so OpenClaw likely isn't even using mcporter to connect to sorftime. I should check how OpenClaw is actually configured to connect to MCP servers.\n","thinkingSignature":"4c7085656336248d7635990f96de92050d803b7359c90dcb189e619c630f6d95"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_izcdm20cqzot_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); channels=d.get('channels',{}); print(json.dumps(channels, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":234,"output":282,"cacheRead":62016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62532,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453806875,"responseId":"066ec4afe67ad3b1eb70939d69c2ae83"}}
