{"type":"message","id":"790b910d","parentId":"33296a03","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:30:39.411Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the actual issue. The cron job calls an agentTurn with a message instructing the agent to run the daily selection workflow. But that workflow might be failing because:\n\n1. The Sorftime MCP config has truncated key\n2. The OpenClaw MCP server for sorftime might not be working properly\n3. There might be errors in the daily selection process\n\nLet me check if there's any recent cron run history or log output. Let me also try to understand why selections aren't succeeding. I should first fix the truncated key in the mcporter config, then check what happens with a test query.\n\nActually, I already confirmed the mcporter call works with the get_time function. But I need to verify the full key is actually being sent. Let me check more carefully.\n\nWait - the mcporter config shows truncated key \"Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" but when I curl with the same truncated key, I get authentication failure. But when I use the full key \"rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09\", get_time works.\n\nSo the question is: does mcporter actually send the full key or the truncated one? I tested get_time via mcporter and it returned the correct time. So mcporter IS sending the full key. The config display is just truncated for privacy but the actual value is correct.\n\nSo the MCP itself is working. The issue must be with the actual selection workflow. The cron job runs every day at 9AM - let me see if there's any recent history.\n\nActually, the user says \"好多天选品不成功\" - many days the selection hasn't succeeded. This could mean:\n1. The cron job runs but produces no results\n2. The cron job fails entirely\n3. Data gets written but nothing passes the filters\n\nLet me check the cron run history.\n","thinkingSignature":"55e4b3a61d66318d5dc113257711b92f7fc9f5a6693194b088e515d6e1de5b9f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r63