{"type":"message","id":"a4a921a1","parentId":"a3937301","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:31:13.856Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the pattern. The first error on 1779325211120 (June 1) was about \"minimax/Min\" - a model configuration error. Then starting from 1779498147622, it's all \"AI service temporarily overloaded\" errors.\n\nThe issue isn't just that the MCP key is broken in config - it's that the model being used for the cron jobs (`minimax/MinMax-M2.7`) is returning \"AI service temporarily overloaded\" for ALL attempts since May 31. This is a consistent failure pattern.\n\nBut wait - the user's saying \"天天失败\" (fails every day). Looking at the run history:\n\n\n- June 1 onwards: almost all errors\n\nThe model being used is `minimax/MinMax-M2.7` per the runtime info at the top.\n\nThis is a model service issue - MiniMax API is consistently overloaded. The user's right - the bot isn't working properly because every cron run is hitting this overload error.\n\nBut the user says \"没有数据\" (no data). Even if the cron job ran successfully, what data would it be fetching? Let me check - the cron job's message says: 抓取Amazon Hair Claws类目数据，按SOP筛选评分，将结果写入飞书多维表AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd/tblHU2do30jzinJT，发送选品报告给用户. So if it ran, it would query sorftime for hair accessories data, filter it, and write to a Feishu table. But the MCP key in the config is truncated and broken. Even if the model worked, the actual API calls would fail.\n\nLet me fix both issues: first, fix the MCP key in the config, then check if the model overload is a separate issue.\n\nLet me test the current session - in this very conversation, I'm responding with MiniMax-M2.7 and it's working fine. So the model overload error might have been a temporary issue from earlier. Let me just fix the config key and try to run the selection manually to get data.\n\nActually, I need to fix the key in mcporter.json first since that's what the MCP uses. The config file seems to have been manually edited at some point and the key got truncated to just the last few characters instead of the full key.\n\nLet me check the current config state and see what's actually there.\n","thinkingSignature":"19fdb2578b9f0050cf03b5bf4340f0fea364c7b1390126fb0cda7cb8f5864629"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c75qtnoek70f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test both the config key AND the actual full key to see which works\necho \"=== Testing truncated key from config ===\"\nmcporter call sorftime-mcp.get_time --config /home/halei/workspace-tts/config/mcporter.json 2>&1\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Testing explicit full key ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://mcp.sorftime.com/\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer rhblyi…qt09\" \\\n  -H \"accept: application/json, text/event-stream\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"get_time\",\"arguments\":{}},\"id\":99}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":524,"output":693,"cacheRead":65664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66881,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780453859057,"responseId":"066ec4e471c099e35510a429a3393c5e"}}
