{"type":"message","id":"ae070bf2","parentId":"178557cd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:35:57.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The filters are too strict. Let me look at the data more carefully to understand what parameters are actually achievable. Let me try a different approach - search TikTok for products and get their details to see if we can find newer entrants.\n\nActually, the real issue seems to be that Hair Claws category on Amazon is dominated by established products with thousands of reviews. The 30-day cutoff might be too strict for this category. Let me check the SOP again - maybe I should focus on a different approach like finding trending products on TikTok and cross-referencing.\n\nActually, let me look at what the cron job was supposed to do and how it was failing. The error was \"AI service temporarily overloaded\" - which might not be a Sorftime issue at all, but a MiniMax API issue. The cron runs at 9AM when many people are using the service. Let me check if there's a fallback model configured.\n\nBut the user is complaining that there are many days with no successful product selection. Let me think about what might be going wrong:\n\n\n1. The API overload errors could mean the cron is just hitting rate limits at peak times\n2. There might be issues with how I'm calling the tools or handling responses\n3. I should try a more flexible search approach to see if I can find products that meet the criteria\n","thinkingSignature":"fb6c2af4682d2eb8239d4afb19420605ec6977d006c876357d17bd7e90125382"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2kapbsdvg55a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test the AI service with a simple query\necho \"Testing AI...\" && date"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":524,"output":309,"cacheRead":82368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","t