{"type":"message","id":"39284d38","parentId":"4fa4f59b","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:37:20.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The JSON is valid up to char 54976, and the truncation happens in the middle of a string. This means we're missing about 13K characters of data. But we have enough to analyze the category structure and identify products. The data we already parsed shows:\n\n- 0 products in 0-30 day range (the category is very mature)\n- 12 products in 30-90 day range\n- These are the closest to \"new entrants\"\n\nSince Hair Claws category is too mature to find products passing the entry window filter, the SOP says the entry window is a pre-filter. If no products pass, we need to broaden the scope.\n\nLet me take a practical approach: since we can't get fresh AI results due to the model overload issue, and the cron job is also failing, let me:\n1. First explain the current situation clearly\n2. Try to do one manual product search to find anything we can\n3. For the cron job failure - the issue is \"AI service temporarily overloaded\" - this might be a transient issue\n\nFor now, let me respond to the user about what I found and what the issues are, and try to find at least some products to show progress.\n\nLet me search with broader parameters - any products in hair accessories that might be new (even if older than 30 days, we can use the SOP's three-step verification on them).\n","thinkingSignature":"950e8e56cae3c3a729e304b0578e02f54e73797016e659ec5dcc32ca296e6ad3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2utc5qiln0fz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get category report truncated correctly - check first 54K chars\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/tmp/cat_report.json') as f:\n    content = f.read()[:54976]\ndata = json.loads(content)\nproducts = data.get('Top100产品', [])\nprint(f'Products parsed: {len(products)}')\nprint(f'Stats: {json.dumps(data.get(\\\"类目统计报告\\\",{}), ensure_ascii=False)[:500]}')\n\""