{"type":"message","id":"94033f7d","parentId":"c3a32be2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T07:49:59.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create a new cron job for the SOP v6.0 workflow. The user accepted the \"hybrid mode\" recommendation:\n- Daytime (9:00-21:00) every 3 hours - 5 times per day\n- Each run uses ~300 MCP calls for phase 1 (30 products max)\n- Daily consumption: ~1500 calls (within budget of 30000/30 = 1000/day but with 30000一次性 purchased, we have more flexibility)\n\nWait, if they purchased 30000 calls一次性, then daily budget isn't 1000 anymore. The 30000 is the total pool. So the daily allocation concept changes - it's about how fast to use the 30000 over time.\n \nWith 30000 total calls and 5 scans per day at 300 calls each, I'm looking at 1500 calls daily, which means the pool would last about 20 days. Let me verify the phase 1 call estimates though - `tiktok_product_trend` might be a single call returning multiple products rather than one call per product, so I should recalculate based on the actual API structure to make sure the estimates are accurate.\n\nFor cron jobs, I should set up multiple runs during daytime hours: 9:00, 12:00, 15:00, 18:00, and 21:00. Each will trigger an agent turn that executes the SOP v6.0 workflow - calling `tiktok_product_trend` for trending products, filtering results, calling Shopee for verification, calling 1688 for supply chain data, and writing the results to a Feishu table.\n\nI also need to disable the existing 9AM job that was using the old SOP.\n","thinkingSignature":"ac82f0f64e30c4f87dc38a7a94915a1e77e64b6ca7757e721145a1adcf651f64"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2tv8y2unw3e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\njobs = d.get('jobs', [])\nfor j in jobs:\n    if 'TK选品' in j.get('name','') or '选品' in j.get('name',''):\n        print('ID:', j.get('id'))\n        print('Name:', j.get('name'))\n        print('Enabled:', j.get('enabled'))\n        print()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":551,"output":483,"cacheRead":95991,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97025,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780472985207,"responseId":"066f0f99804d64d3ff8207ee1a5da041"}}
