{"type":"message","id":"a557898b","parentId":"6cc02c6a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T08:03:34.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still NOTEXIST. Even with minimal fields it fails. This strongly suggests it's a permissions/auth issue, not a data format issue.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user says the bot has edit permissions. I verified that `list` works with the app_token. But `create` fails.\n\nMaybe the issue is that the user identity (OAuth) context doesn't have write access, even though the bot app does. The `feishu_bitable_app_table_record` tool says it's \"以用户身份\" (as user identity). So it uses the user's OAuth token, not the bot's token.\n\nIf the user's OAuth token only has read permissions, then even though the bot has edit permissions on the bitable, the tool can't write because it's using the user's token.\n\nThe user needs to grant write permissions to the Feishu app. This might require re-running the OAuth authorization flow or using `feishu_oauth_batch_auth`.\n\nLet me suggest the `feishu_oauth_batch_auth` approach to the user, since they said \"不可能，你是可编辑权限，我看了\" (implying they believe the permissions are correct).","thinkingSignature":"24cac4d09fbd12119e4a95b7f39dec5af29f817303dff4334d2f1bb0083338a9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n还是失败。这个错误持续出现，说明不是字段格式问题，而是**权限上下文问题**。\n\n`list` 能读 → app_token 正确，读权限OK\n`create` 失败 → **写权限问题**\n\n这个 bitable 工具是「以用户身份」执行，用的是你的 OAuth token，不是 bot token。可能你的 OAuth token 只有读权限没有写权限。\n\n飞书批量授权工具可以一次性授权所有权限。要不要试一下？\n\n---\n\n**可能的原因：**\n你的飞书 OAuth 授权只给了读取权限，没有给写入权限。Bot 本身有编辑权限，但工具运行时用的是你的用户 token，所以写操作被拒绝。\n\n**解决方案：**\n用 `feishu_oauth_batch_auth` 一次性授权所有权限，或者去飞书开放平台重新授权应用写入权限。\n\n要我现在用这个工具吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":955,"output":402,"cacheRead":132672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134029,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780473803514,"respo