a completely different table to see if this is a table-specific problem or a broader permission issue.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the error itself - \"NOTEXIST\" could mean the app doesn't have access to the data table, the table has some kind of protection or approval workflow enabled, or there's a version mismatch issue. Since the user mentioned they switched to \"manageable mode,\" I'm thinking this might be related to approval requirements that are blocking write operations.\n\nBut wait - the user said they already switched it and it still doesn't work. Let me look at what that mode actually does. \"可管理模式\" (Manageable Mode) in Feishu Bitable typically means the app has admin-level access with fewer restrictions. If that doesn't resolve it, maybe there's a workspace configuration issue preventing the bot from writing to this particular bitable, or perhaps it's in a space that requires different permissions. At this point I should probably ask the user directly if they can write to the table themselves to isolate whether it's a permission issue or something else.","thinkingSignature":"ea0c27a4e7411318742e4476ddd653ed63856c538862bbccd991f07d81912a2b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n还是 NOTEXIST。让我换个方式排查——先确认 app_token 本身没问题：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d8da747ee0df41be8385577f","name":"feishu_bitable_app","arguments":{"action":"get","app_token":"***"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":377,"output":739,"cacheRead":131456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780481510291,"responseId":"066f30e752fe7b13d145824af22a0c53"}}
