{"type":"message","id":"626b4afe","parentId":"c70cca40","timestamp":"2026-06-03T10:55:43.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that the table permissions should be fine and they can see me (the bot) in the permissions list. So the bot DOES have access. But my create calls keep failing with NOTEXIST.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user confirmed:\n1. The bot has edit permissions on the bitable\n2. They can see the bot in the permissions list\n3. They switched the bitable to manageable mode\n\nBut I keep getting NOTEXIST. What else could be wrong?\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that I need to check if the app_token is actually correct. The user shared the URL: https://my.feishu.cn/base/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd\n\nThe app_token is `AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd`.\n\nBut maybe there's a different issue. Let me think... \n\nActually, wait - I just realized something. The user said \"然后我看你也在这个权限里边\" (and I can see you in the permissions). This suggests they checked the bitable sharing settings and confirmed the bot is there.\n\nBut NOTEXIST error is strange. Let me think about what NOTEXIST could mean in this context:\n- The record doesn't exist (but we're creating, not reading)\n- The table doesn't exist (but list works)\n- Some required parameter is missing or wrong\n- The app doesn't have permission to perform the specific action\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is with the \"预估利润\" field. Looking back at the field list:\n- \"field_name\": \"预估利润\" - this is the correct name\n\nBut wait - I just noticed in my field mapping earlier I had \"IP地址\" but the actual field is \"IP地址\" (with IP in Chinese). Let me check the actual field name again...\n\nFrom the field list I got earlier:\n```\n{\n  \"field_id\": \"fldBpONRvx\",\n  \"field_name\": \"预估利润\",\n  \"type\": 2,\n  \"ui_type\": \"Number\"\n}\n```\n\nSo the field name is \"预估利润\" which is what I've been using. That's correct.\n\nWait - let me look at the field list more carefully. I got the field list earlier:\n```\n{\"field_id\": \"fldipZCSu3\", \"field_name\": \"采集状态\", \"type\": 3, ...}\n{\"field_id\": \"fldBGJUhdL\", \"field_name\": \"1688价格(CNY)\", \"type\": 2, ...}\n```\n\nSo I have all the field names correct. Let me try a completely different approach - maybe there's a syntax error in my JSON or something. Let me try a minimal record creation with just a couple fields.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the error more carefully. NOTEXIST. In Feishu's API, this error code typically means \"resource does not exist\". But for a create operation, this is weird because we're trying to CREATE a new record, not access an existing one.\n\nUnless... the table itself is somehow not accessible for writes? But the user says the bot has edit permissions...\n\nOh wait! I just thought of something. Maybe the issue is that the bitable is in a **Wiki** (知识库) rather than a regular bitable? Wiki bitables sometimes have different permission models. The URL the user shared was `https://my.feishu.cn/base/...` which is a regular bitable URL, not a wiki URL.\n\nActually, looking at the field list again - the fields include \"IP地址\" (IP risk) which has options like \"无\" and \"待确认\". And \"行动建议\" with various options like \"正常采购首单30-50件\" etc. These are all SingleSelect fields that should accept string values.\n\nLet me try once more but this time with a very simple record - just a couple fields to see if it works. If even that fails, then the issue is definitely not with the field values.\n\nLet me just try once cleanly.","thinkingSignature":"ddfc5b9725fa63263206054bc73bb0a871601bee3db9b6401dadae629ae08987"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你说权限没问题，bot 也在权限列表里。那问题可能不在权限上。\n\n让我试一个最简单的写入，就两三个字段，排除法排查：\n\napp_token = `AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd`\ntable_id = `tblHU2do30jzinJT`\n\n只写商品名称和月销量两个字段试试：\n\n| 等级 | 商品 | TikTok月销 |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| **S** | 发带(1733133706895197735) | 25,902 |\n\n---\n\n如果这个也失败，我就真的找不到原因了，只能让你手动录入，同时记录这个问题后续排查。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":630,"output":975,"cacheRead":143168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":144773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780484129655,"responseId":"066f3b224f28ebdcf352c3f44fe6c7f5"}}
